TY  - JOUR
T1  - Optimal Production and Inventory Policy for Multiple Products Under Resource Constraints
AU  - DeCroix, Gregory A.
AU  - Arreola-Risa, Antonio
Y1  - 1998/07/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.44.7.950
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.44.7.950
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 950
EP  - 961
VL  - 44
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We show that a modified base-stock policy is optimal for multiproduct, infinite-horizon production-inventory systems, where demand for the products is random and the products share a finite resource every period. We characterize the optimal policy for the case of homogeneous products. Because of the difficulty in computing the optimal base-stock levels for the heterogeneous case, we propose a heuristic that is simple enough for practical applications. We present numerical results that suggest that the heuristic yields near-optimal solutions.
AB  - We show that a modified base-stock policy is optimal for multiproduct, infinite-horizon production-inventory systems, where demand for the products is random and the products share a finite resource every period. We characterize the optimal policy for the case of homogeneous products. Because of the difficulty in computing the optimal base-stock levels for the heterogeneous case, we propose a heuristic that is simple enough for practical applications. We present numerical results that suggest that the heuristic yields near-optimal solutions.
